    "Congressional gift rules layer a source-based ban on top of the general dollar limits: while members and staff may generally accept gifts under $50 (with a $100 annual aggregate from one source), gifts from registered lobbyists or entities that employ them are prohibited outright. A staffer at a firm with a registered lobbyist therefore cannot rely on the under-$50 allowance. The first compliance question is who the source is, not how small the amount is.",
